{
  "esm": "0.1.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "MassActionSubstrateCancellation",
    "description": "Cross-binding conformance fixture (esm-06a): mass-action lowering must apply the substrate product to EVERY reaction per esm-spec.md §7.4, even when the rate field references a substrate (cancellation form). Old behavior in Python+Julia+Rust used a detect-and-skip heuristic that returned `k/A` unchanged, producing dynamics independent of B and yielding NaN at A=0 (the geoschem_fullchem R12 pathology). This fixture asserts the spec-conformant analytic trajectory; binding bindings whose runner still implements the heuristic will fail it.",
    "authors": ["esm-06a conformance"],
    "tags": ["conformance", "mass-action", "substrate-cancellation", "esm-06a", "esm-uwe"]
  },
  "reaction_systems": {
    "CancellationSystem": {
      "reference": {
        "notes": "Reaction A + B -> C with rate `k/A` (cancellation form). Per spec §7.4 the runner multiplies by the substrate product, giving effective rate v = (k/A)*A*B = k*B. Analytic solution from A(0)=2, B(0)=1, C(0)=0 with k=0.5: dB/dt = -k*B ⇒ B(t) = exp(-k*t); dA/dt = dB/dt ⇒ A(t) = 1 + exp(-k*t); C(t) = 1 - exp(-k*t)."
      },
      "species": {
        "A": {
          "units": "1",
          "default": 2.0,
          "description": "Substrate that appears in the rate denominator (cancellation pattern)."
        },
        "B": {
          "units": "1",
          "default": 1.0,
          "description": "Co-substrate; effective decay rate after cancellation is k*B."
        },
        "C": {
          "units": "1",
          "default": 0.0,
          "description": "Product."
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "k": {
          "units": "1/s",
          "default": 0.5,
          "description": "Rate coefficient. Per spec, the runner forms the full rate law k * ∏Sᵢ^nᵢ from this coefficient and the substrate stoichiometry."
        }
      },
      "reactions": [
        {
          "id": "R0",
          "name": "cancellation_step",
          "substrates": [
            {"species": "A", "stoichiometry": 1},
            {"species": "B", "stoichiometry": 1}
          ],
          "products": [
            {"species": "C", "stoichiometry": 1}
          ],
          "rate": {
            "op": "/",
            "args": ["k", "A"]
          }
        }
      ],
      "tolerance": {"rel": 1.0e-6, "abs": 1.0e-10},
      "tests": [
        {
          "id": "spec_conformant_cancellation",
          "description": "Analytic-reference trajectory under spec §7.4 mass-action: A(t) = 1 + exp(-0.5 t), B(t) = exp(-0.5 t), C(t) = 1 - exp(-0.5 t). The old detect-and-skip heuristic produced rate = k/A unmodified (no B dependence), giving a strictly different trajectory — a binding that still applies the heuristic will miss every t>0 assertion.",
          "initial_conditions": {"A": 2.0, "B": 1.0, "C": 0.0},
          "parameter_overrides": {"k": 0.5},
          "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 5.0},
          "assertions": [
            {"variable": "A", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2.0},
            {"variable": "B", "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0},
            {"variable": "C", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0},
            {"variable": "A", "time": 1.0, "expected": 1.6065306597126334},
            {"variable": "B", "time": 1.0, "expected": 0.6065306597126334},
            {"variable": "C", "time": 1.0, "expected": 0.3934693402873666},
            {"variable": "A", "time": 5.0, "expected": 1.0820849986238988},
            {"variable": "B", "time": 5.0, "expected": 0.0820849986238988},
            {"variable": "C", "time": 5.0, "expected": 0.9179150013761012}
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "domains": {
    "default": {
      "temporal": {},
      "initial_conditions": {
        "type": "per_variable",
        "values": {
          "CancellationSystem.A": 2.0,
          "CancellationSystem.B": 1.0,
          "CancellationSystem.C": 0.0
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
